WEBVTT

00:33.950 --> 00:35.535
How was the festival?

00:35.577 --> 00:37.037
It was...

00:37.078 --> 00:38.204
it was amazing.

00:38.246 --> 00:39.956
She's a little nervous.

00:39.998 --> 00:42.542
She's waiting to hear back from
    her manager about her script.

00:42.584 --> 00:44.335
Drew's a great guy,
         but his client list

00:44.377 --> 00:45.628
could use more women of color.

00:45.670 --> 00:46.796
What she's saying is,

00:46.838 --> 00:48.214
he is only interested
            in signing me

00:48.256 --> 00:50.550
because folks are hiring
           Black writers now.

00:50.592 --> 00:52.761
I like you. I'd be willing
        to take you on board.

00:52.802 --> 00:55.221
Don't we need to have
           a conversation?

00:55.263 --> 00:58.224
I think Valentina has run
       her course on the show.

00:58.266 --> 00:59.517
Did I do something wrong?

00:59.559 --> 01:01.895
So, how are you two?

01:01.936 --> 01:04.397
Uh...we're great.

01:11.446 --> 01:14.407
Maybe if I close my eyes

01:14.449 --> 01:16.534
In the morning

01:16.576 --> 01:20.747
This won't be reality

01:20.789 --> 01:24.250
Mm, 'cause it's like
         the moon last night

01:24.292 --> 01:26.419
Oh, my gosh.

01:26.461 --> 01:28.922
Is this it?

01:28.963 --> 01:30.090
I think so.

01:30.131 --> 01:32.842
Well, now it can't be.
           It's bad luck.

01:32.884 --> 01:34.427
I don't believe
          in superstitions.

01:34.469 --> 01:35.970
It's real.

01:38.056 --> 01:39.140
It's not.

01:48.441 --> 01:50.610
So...

01:50.652 --> 01:54.531
did you explore while
      I was away at Moondance?

01:56.658 --> 01:57.867
Did you?

02:07.460 --> 02:10.672
What do you want me to do?

02:10.713 --> 02:12.006
Go and sleep with a guy

02:12.048 --> 02:14.968
just so I can tell you
        how much I hated it?

02:15.009 --> 02:17.637
I just want you to be honest
           with yourself.

02:19.514 --> 02:22.183
I just wanna be happy.

02:23.893 --> 02:28.064
Does the idea of marrying me
           make you happy?

02:30.650 --> 02:32.152
I don't know.

02:36.865 --> 02:38.533
Does it make you happy?

02:46.124 --> 02:47.876
It makes me nervous.

02:49.961 --> 02:51.171
Me too.

02:53.506 --> 02:56.634
Then what are we doing?

02:56.676 --> 02:58.052
I don't know.

03:06.853 --> 03:10.315
I just know that I love you.

03:10.356 --> 03:13.193
I love you too.

03:13.234 --> 03:17.864
Instead of doing what
   we think we're supposed to do,

03:17.906 --> 03:20.825
for once,

03:20.867 --> 03:24.704
let's do what we want to do.

03:24.746 --> 03:28.666
And what is that?

03:28.708 --> 03:30.668
Not get married.

03:34.047 --> 03:37.091
-Deal.

03:51.189 --> 03:53.233
Our song.

03:53.274 --> 03:55.526
I was gonna surprise you
    with our song at the wedding,

03:55.568 --> 03:58.321
but...

03:58.363 --> 04:01.032
since that's not happening,

04:01.074 --> 04:04.077
I figured we could have our
   first and last dance right now.

04:04.118 --> 04:06.913
Constantly

04:11.960 --> 04:16.130
I think about you
             all the time

04:16.172 --> 04:20.301
Constantly
          you're on my mind

04:20.343 --> 04:23.096
How do you think
      people are gonna take it?

04:23.137 --> 04:26.599
-Take what?
          -Us breaking up.

04:26.641 --> 04:29.644
Mm-mm-mm.

04:29.686 --> 04:31.521
They'll be fine.

04:32.897 --> 04:35.900
First I lose my job,
            and now this?

04:35.942 --> 04:39.112
When is Mercury
      gonna stop retrograding?

04:39.153 --> 04:41.906
upbeat music

04:45.493 --> 04:47.120
-Thanks.
              -Mm-hmm.

04:51.916 --> 04:54.085
I still can't believe
         you told Nia first.

04:54.127 --> 04:55.628
I'm feeling some kind of way.

04:55.670 --> 04:57.297
We were on her vision board.

04:57.338 --> 04:58.631
You knew?

04:58.673 --> 05:01.134
Girl, everybody knew.
                Yeah.

05:01.175 --> 05:03.761
Marie, how are you
             so relaxed?

05:03.803 --> 05:05.221
I'm devastated.

05:05.263 --> 05:07.473
Probably 'cause she got
           other options.

05:07.515 --> 05:08.975
I love Chuck.
            I really do.

05:09.017 --> 05:10.977
-I will always love Chuck.
         -Come on, Whitney.

05:11.019 --> 05:12.437
But after we had
         that conversation,

05:12.478 --> 05:13.604
I just felt happy.

05:13.646 --> 05:15.106
Mm. Come on.
              For real.

05:15.148 --> 05:16.649
I felt like
        I had a new attitude.

05:16.691 --> 05:17.984
Yes, Patti!

05:18.026 --> 05:19.485
I'm sad
          to see Chuck go,

05:19.527 --> 05:21.654
but I'm also really excited
    to get back out there again.

05:21.696 --> 05:23.823
There's nothing out there.

05:23.865 --> 05:25.491
Don't you have two dudes
       knocking down your door

05:25.533 --> 05:26.659
-right now?
               -Right.

05:26.701 --> 05:28.494
Yeah. One of them is Ben.

05:28.536 --> 05:29.871
-Sorry.
               -Yeah.

05:29.912 --> 05:31.039
And the other one is Tristan,

05:31.080 --> 05:32.957
who is still
         all over the place.

05:32.999 --> 05:35.043
I can't welcome new energy
            into my house

05:35.084 --> 05:36.669
until I settle
         this shit with Ida

05:36.711 --> 05:38.129
and get my sister
         off my damn couch.

05:38.171 --> 05:40.089
I still can't believe
         that she fired you.

05:40.131 --> 05:41.883
Neither can I.

05:41.924 --> 05:43.926
You know what, I hear that
      she gets jealous of women

05:43.968 --> 05:45.762
that she thinks are
         prettier than her.

05:45.803 --> 05:47.638
I don't think that's it.

05:47.680 --> 05:49.182
Do you, Hattie?

05:49.223 --> 05:51.309
I think that
         you should look at

05:51.351 --> 05:53.978
being away from her
     toxic energy as a blessing.

05:54.020 --> 05:56.272
Getting cast in something else
        would be a blessing.

05:56.314 --> 05:57.648
-It would.
               -Yeah.

05:57.690 --> 05:59.525
Aren't you gonna talk
     to your new boo about that?

05:59.567 --> 06:01.319
Ben is not my new boo.

06:01.361 --> 06:03.780
And all he has is an idea.
   It's not even a real thing yet.

06:03.821 --> 06:05.114
You shouldn't
         get your hopes up,

06:05.156 --> 06:06.949
'cause I doubt
     it'll ever be a real thing.

06:06.991 --> 06:09.035
Negative Nancy
     has entered the group chat.

06:09.077 --> 06:11.871
-Don't call me that.
      -Stop being so negative.

06:11.913 --> 06:13.539
A'ight.
       I'm late for a meeting.

06:13.581 --> 06:15.500
Gotta go. Bye.

06:15.541 --> 06:16.876
-Okay, bye.
           -Love you too.

06:16.918 --> 06:19.504
upbeat percussive music

06:22.799 --> 06:24.258
Do you think this is
         a good photo for me

06:24.300 --> 06:25.927
to tell the world I'll no
    longer be on   Cocoa's Butter   ?

06:25.968 --> 06:27.428
Yeah, you look real pitiful
            in this one.

06:28.805 --> 06:30.681
My emo posts
     always get the most likes.

06:30.723 --> 06:33.226
Mm, I gotta go.
        I got a meeting too.

06:33.267 --> 06:35.103
Okay, bye.

06:35.144 --> 06:37.647
Hey, look at us,
       with meetings and shit.

06:37.688 --> 06:40.274
-Right?
               -Right?

06:40.316 --> 06:41.484
Ooh.

06:46.864 --> 06:49.242
It's basically a movie
        about a happy family

06:49.283 --> 06:52.703
on a mission
     to find eternal happiness.

06:52.745 --> 06:54.747
-Do you have a writer?
           -Making a list.

06:54.789 --> 06:56.416
Send it over by end of day.

06:58.084 --> 06:59.001
Marie?

06:59.043 --> 07:00.336
Quintrell and I sat down

07:00.378 --> 07:02.213
with a writer we really liked
           the other day.

07:02.255 --> 07:04.757
She's already read the book,
          and she loves it.

07:04.799 --> 07:05.925
Does she have time
            to adapt it?

07:05.967 --> 07:07.260
We're still trying
          to find that out.

07:07.301 --> 07:09.220
And he's totally over
           this whole idea

07:09.262 --> 07:11.180
-of financing it himself?
            -Yes.

07:11.222 --> 07:13.099
Now, he does still want to
    put in some of his own money,

07:13.141 --> 07:14.934
but he's down to let us pay
        for everything else.

07:14.976 --> 07:16.436
He wants us to provide
         the infrastructure

07:16.477 --> 07:18.229
and make sure nothing
      slips through the cracks.

07:18.271 --> 07:20.773
-Great. Thank you for that.
             -Of course.

07:20.815 --> 07:24.110
Oh, and I already have talent
      attached to   Happy People.

07:24.152 --> 07:26.904
Oh, that's the actual title?

07:26.946 --> 07:28.448
Working title.

07:28.489 --> 07:29.782
I should hope so.

07:29.824 --> 07:32.201
Who do you have attached?

07:32.243 --> 07:34.328
Nia Baptiste.

07:34.370 --> 07:36.706
-Nia is not a name.
         -But she should be.

07:36.747 --> 07:38.249
You're right,
      but she's not right now,

07:38.291 --> 07:40.209
so she can't help you
        get your movie made.

07:40.251 --> 07:42.336
Yeah, it would take a lot
      to get Ben's movie made.

07:42.378 --> 07:44.297
What? I thought you said
        it was a sure thing.

07:44.338 --> 07:46.007
You don't even have a script.

07:46.048 --> 07:48.468
Ben, I'm all
        for uplifting movies,

07:48.509 --> 07:52.388
but right now,
     your idea is a little thin.

07:52.430 --> 07:55.266
White people make thin movies
   all the time, so why can't we?

07:55.308 --> 07:57.143
Come on.
    Don't make this a race thing.

07:57.185 --> 07:59.103
Spoken like a true white guy.

08:01.022 --> 08:03.483
Since when did you
           become so woke?

08:03.524 --> 08:06.486
Don't use that word.

08:06.527 --> 08:10.740
Look, I need you both
   to bring me some better ideas.

08:11.407 --> 08:14.452
Here's one: if you don't
    make my movie, I'm quitting.

08:14.494 --> 08:16.787
Yeah.
         What are you, five?

08:16.829 --> 08:18.080
No. I'm serious.

08:18.122 --> 08:20.333
-You're being ridiculous.
              -Try me.

08:23.211 --> 08:24.420
Oh, come on.

08:24.462 --> 08:25.880
-Ben.
             -Nah.

08:27.798 --> 08:30.134
-Wow.

08:30.176 --> 08:33.638
Do you actually think
             he'll quit?

08:33.679 --> 08:36.849
I don't know. We'll cross
   that bridge when we get to it.

08:44.774 --> 08:46.359
What?

08:49.111 --> 08:51.030
Chuck and I broke up.

08:53.199 --> 08:54.867
Why?

08:54.909 --> 08:57.495
What do you mean?

08:57.537 --> 08:59.080
I just--

08:59.121 --> 09:03.209
What, you think that
    I broke up with him for you?

09:03.251 --> 09:06.796
I mean,
     I don't know what to think.

09:06.837 --> 09:10.299
He and I both
          realized that...

09:10.341 --> 09:13.636
we have a lot of growing to do.

09:13.678 --> 09:15.304
I get that.

09:17.890 --> 09:19.433
I'm so sorry.

09:22.728 --> 09:25.022
Is that it?

09:25.064 --> 09:29.193
I mean,
    do you want there to be more?

09:29.235 --> 09:30.319
I guess I just thought

09:30.361 --> 09:33.573
you'd have more to say
             than that.

09:36.117 --> 09:40.079
I have a great deal
     of respect for you, Marie.

09:40.121 --> 09:42.999
Okay? I really do.

09:43.040 --> 09:44.542
I don't want this to get weird.

09:44.584 --> 09:47.420
I just want us to thrive
        and make good movies.

09:47.461 --> 09:50.214
somber music

10:04.854 --> 10:07.231
Your script has gotten
   so much better since last time.

10:07.273 --> 10:08.774
I told you
         I was gon' get it.

10:08.816 --> 10:10.526
And get it, you did.

10:10.568 --> 10:13.446
I think you're ready
            for generals.

10:13.487 --> 10:16.449
Are you sure we can't just
    skip the getting-to-know-yous

10:16.490 --> 10:19.118
and go straight to the meetings
    that are gonna get me a job?

10:19.160 --> 10:21.287
You gotta crawl
        before you can walk.

10:21.329 --> 10:23.706
Well, I feel like I've been
      doing plenty of crawling.

10:23.748 --> 10:27.001
You got a lot more
           crawling to do.

10:27.835 --> 10:29.795
But you are making progress.

10:29.837 --> 10:32.048
Chin up, young Jedi.

10:32.089 --> 10:33.799
Also, you don't have
       to come into my office

10:33.841 --> 10:35.134
for every little thing.

10:35.176 --> 10:36.969
I mean, this meeting
       could've been an email;

10:37.011 --> 10:38.596
our last meeting
        could've been a text.

10:38.638 --> 10:40.222
Well, I mean, I ain't got
          shit else to do.

10:40.264 --> 10:41.641
Shit, I need to get a job

10:41.682 --> 10:45.436
so I can get out
     this white girl apartment.

10:45.478 --> 10:46.812
All in due time.

10:46.854 --> 10:48.272
You're getting there.

10:48.314 --> 10:50.524
-Hmm.

10:50.566 --> 10:52.318
It's probably a bill collector
             right now.

10:52.360 --> 10:54.153
Just answer it.
     Pretend like you don't know

10:54.195 --> 10:55.988
-who the hell Hattie is.
      -Well, I tried that once,

10:56.030 --> 10:57.448
but then when
      they said my name again,

10:57.490 --> 10:59.158
I forgot to pretend like
      I didn't know who I was,

10:59.200 --> 11:00.785
and I accidentally responded
           to my own name,

11:00.826 --> 11:02.662
and they was like, "What?"
       And I was like, "Huh?"

11:02.703 --> 11:04.288
And then I got nervous
            and hung up.

11:04.330 --> 11:06.165
Look, I'ma take this,
             all right?

11:06.207 --> 11:07.708
I look forward
         to those generals.

11:07.750 --> 11:09.627
And I look forward
         to setting them up.

11:09.669 --> 11:12.463
jazz music

11:13.673 --> 11:15.675
Hello?

11:15.716 --> 11:17.802
Is that my daughter?

11:17.843 --> 11:19.178
Dad?

11:19.220 --> 11:21.013
Why you answering
        the phone all scary?

11:21.055 --> 11:23.182
What, you thought I was
   a bill collector or something?

11:23.224 --> 11:24.433
Yeah, I did.

11:24.475 --> 11:26.894
I just landed in LA.
           What you doing?

11:26.936 --> 11:28.396
Minding my business.

11:28.437 --> 11:30.856
Well, do you got time
           to see your daddy?

11:30.898 --> 11:33.484
I-I guess so.

11:33.526 --> 11:35.361
Well, let me know where you at,
      and I'ma pull up on you.

11:35.403 --> 11:37.154
It's been way too long.

11:37.196 --> 11:39.156
All right.
           I'll text you.

11:39.198 --> 11:41.826
See you later, Gator.

11:41.867 --> 11:43.202
Bye.

11:52.002 --> 11:54.380
That's right, Weezy.

11:54.422 --> 11:56.215
You better get George.

11:56.257 --> 11:58.551
You know he ain't got no sense.

11:58.592 --> 11:59.885
Yeah!

12:04.140 --> 12:05.766
What's wrong?

12:05.808 --> 12:08.561
-Guess who just called me.
     -Whoopi Goldberg.

12:08.602 --> 12:10.438
No. My dad.

12:11.939 --> 12:14.358
-What that fool want?
       -I don't know.

12:14.400 --> 12:16.569
He said he wanted to see me.

12:16.610 --> 12:19.238
He ain't seen you
            in 10 years.

12:19.280 --> 12:20.740
What he want now?

12:20.781 --> 12:21.907
I don't know.

12:21.949 --> 12:23.409
Don't give that fool
               no money.

12:23.451 --> 12:25.453
I ain't got no money to give.

12:25.494 --> 12:28.748
When you see his ass,
      you tell him to call me.

12:28.789 --> 12:29.957
Why?

12:29.999 --> 12:31.834
He still owe me
     for that pack of cigarettes

12:31.876 --> 12:33.085
I bought him in '92.

12:35.212 --> 12:36.881
Bye, Ma.
             I love you.

12:36.922 --> 12:39.258
All right, I love you too.
      Don't give him no money!

12:41.969 --> 12:45.598
Whoo! Don't make no sense. Look
               at it.

12:45.639 --> 12:46.932
